 small submarines in an advanced stage of construction. reported four submarines about 150 feet in length on the building ways at the Kiangnan shipyard in Shanghai. The hulls of the submarines were completed and internal equipment was being installed.\n\nCommunist China has also built, with considerable Soviet help, 21 modern long-range W-class submarines, but this program was apparently terminated about mid-1960. Although little is known of other programs, China did receive Soviet plans for at least one new class of submarine in 1958 and received marine equipment from the USSR, at least through September 1960. If the four small submarines are in as advanced a stage as reported, they will probably be completed in 1961 with or without further Soviet aid", "token_count": 131, "token_end_0based": 146, "token_start_0based": 16, "token_text": "communist china communist china may have a new class of small submarines in an advanced stage of construction reported four submarines about 150 feet in length on the building ways at the kiangnan shipyard in shanghai the hulls of the submarines were completed and internal equipment was being installed communist china has also built with considerable soviet help 21 modern long-range w-class submarines but this program was apparently terminated about mid-1960 although little is known of other programs china did receive soviet plans for at least one new class of submarine in 1958 and received marine equipment from the ussr at least through september 1960 if the four small submarines are in as advanced a stage as reported they will probably be completed in 1961 with or without further soviet aid", "unred_source_page": 7}
